1
00:00:02,559 --> 00:00:06,519
Torchwood, outside the government,
beyond the police.

2
00:00:06,519 --> 00:00:08,880
Tracking down alien life on earth,

3
00:00:08,880 --> 00:00:11,919
arming the human race
against the future.

4
00:00:11,919 --> 00:00:15,040
The 21st century is when
everything changes...

5
00:00:15,040 --> 00:00:16,519
and you've got to be ready.

6
00:00:16,519 --> 00:00:20,999
This programme contains
some strong language.

7
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:25,519
Hello there.

8
00:01:29,440 --> 00:01:33,320
Apologies for the
unplanned touchdown,
just hit some rotten turbulence.

9
00:01:33,320 --> 00:01:35,160
I'm Captain Jack Harkness.

10
00:01:35,160 --> 00:01:36,919
Diane Holmes, pilot.

11
00:01:36,919 --> 00:01:39,279
Is this some sort of secret base?

12
00:01:39,279 --> 00:01:41,319
You must show me round one day.

13
00:01:41,319 --> 00:01:44,320
Everything all right?
How long before we head off again?

14
00:01:44,320 --> 00:01:47,440
My Uncle's expecting me.
When did you leave?

15
00:01:47,440 --> 00:01:49,519
About half an hour ago. Which date?

16
00:01:51,119 --> 00:01:53,599
Today, December the 18th.
Which year?

17
00:01:55,159 --> 00:01:58,280
Which year?
Which year? I need to know.

18
00:01:59,880 --> 00:02:01,879
1953.

19
00:02:17,319 --> 00:02:19,759
There's no need to be frightened.

20
00:02:19,759 --> 00:02:22,359
Who are you exactly?

21
00:02:22,359 --> 00:02:24,679
The least you know about us,
the better.

22
00:02:26,400 --> 00:02:29,400
Meet the team. Toshiko.

23
00:02:29,400 --> 00:02:31,320
Gwen. Doctor Owen Harper.

24
00:02:31,320 --> 00:02:33,120
John Ellis.

25
00:02:33,120 --> 00:02:35,359
Emma Louise Cowell.

26
00:02:35,359 --> 00:02:37,000
Diane Holmes.

27
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:38,880
Please, follow me.

28
00:02:48,399 --> 00:02:50,800
At least it wasn't a spaceship
full of aliens.

29
00:02:50,800 --> 00:02:52,480
That might have been easier.

30
00:02:52,480 --> 00:02:54,880
But how can you travel
50 years in half an hour?

31
00:02:54,880 --> 00:02:59,720
Your aircraft slipped through
a transcendental portal. A what?
A door in time and space.

32
00:02:59,720 --> 00:03:04,159
It's some kind of trick,
it has to be. Tosh?

33
00:03:06,120 --> 00:03:10,600
Celebrations of the Millennium
in your respective home cities,

34
00:03:10,600 --> 00:03:14,200
photographs documenting the
development of Cardiff Bay

35
00:03:14,200 --> 00:03:18,360
from the '50s to the present day,
blueprints of modern day aeroplanes.

36
00:03:18,360 --> 00:03:20,520
But if all this is true...

37
00:03:20,520 --> 00:03:23,720
then how do we get back? You don't.

38
00:03:23,720 --> 00:03:29,200
According to history, your plane
never returned. I'm sorry.

39
00:03:29,200 --> 00:03:30,959
What's going to happen to us?

40
00:03:32,840 --> 00:03:35,439
Never mind about us.

41
00:03:35,439 --> 00:03:38,400
What happened to everyone else?

42
00:03:38,400 --> 00:03:39,879
Our families.

43
00:03:42,360 --> 00:03:47,040
Your father died in 1959. He was 48.

44
00:03:47,040 --> 00:03:48,999
Dad said he'd die young.

45
00:03:48,999 --> 00:03:51,360
All the men in the
munitions factory did.

46
00:03:51,360 --> 00:03:53,480
Your mother lived
till she was 81 though.

47
00:03:54,880 --> 00:03:58,200
I know this is hard to take in.
But is there anyone else?

48
00:03:58,200 --> 00:04:00,079
My son, Alan Ellis.

49
00:04:00,079 --> 00:04:06,279
He was born on the 6th of April,
1937, 14 Park Place, Grangetown.

50
00:04:06,279 --> 00:04:08,479
He might still be alive.

51
00:04:08,479 --> 00:04:11,840
The archives in the '50s
weren't that well documented.

52
00:04:11,840 --> 00:04:13,399
We'll try again tomorrow.

53
